{"lemma": "أَرْنَبٌ", "slug": "أَرْنَبٌ", "root": "#.ر.ن.ب", "root_slug": "_-ر-ن-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/_-ر-ن-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n16760"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "rabbit", "fa": "خرگوش", "ur": "خرگوش", "tr": "tavşan", "id": "kelinci", "bn": "খরগোশ", "es": "conejo", "fr": "lapin", "de": "Hase", "ru": "кролик", "zh": "兔子"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "rabbit (mammal)"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "1 million EGP", "tags": ["Egypt", "dated", "slang"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From Proto-Semitic *ʔarnab-. Compare Hebrew אַרְנָב (ʾarnā́ḇ)."}, "ipa": ["/ʔar.nab/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n16760", "headword_ar": "اَرْنَبٌ", "root": "rnb", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "[The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hare;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and now applied to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rabbit"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also;]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain animal,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "well known,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, A, K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EnAq", "text_ar": "عناق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[?],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having short fore legs and long hind legs, that treads the ground with the hinder parts of its"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hind"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "legs:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain very prolific animal, called in Pers."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xrkw$", "text_ar": "خركوش"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xaroGuw$o", "text_ar": "خَرْگُوشْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]:"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is said that it is one year a male and another year a female, and menstruates like women; and its fore legs are shorter than its hind legs: when it sleeps, it keeps its eyes open; and when it is sick, it eats green canes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSab", "text_ar": "قَصَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "),"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and its sickness ceases:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Kzw:) the word is a gen. n., (TA,) of the fem. gender, (Msb, TA,) accord. to El-Jáhidh; (TA;) but (Msb) applied to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "male"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "female;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, A, K, TA;) as is also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aronabapN", "text_ar": "اَرْنَبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) which is a dial. var.: (Mgh, Msb:) or to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "female"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[only]; the male being called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xuzazN", "text_ar": "خُزَزٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (T, M, K, TA;) accord. to Lth; but others allow its application to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "male:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T:) the female is also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eikori$apN", "text_ar": "عِكْرِشَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and the young,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xironiqN", "text_ar": "خِرْنِقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^araAnibu", "text_ar": "اَرَانِبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^araAnK", "text_ar": "اَرَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Lh, S, M, K,) the latter, like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vaEaAlK", "text_ar": "ثَعَالٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vaEaAlibu", "text_ar": "ثَعَالِبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", occurring in poetry, (S, M, *) and not allowed by Sb except in poetry. (M.) The"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A", "text_ar": "ا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aronabN", "text_ar": "اَرْنَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is augmentative, accord. to Lth: accord. to most of the grammarians it is disjunctive, (so in a copy of the T and in the TA,) or radical: (so in another copy of the T:) Lth says that no word commences with a radical"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A", "text_ar": "ا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but such as"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1165}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is triliteral; as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aroDN", "text_ar": "اَرْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aro$N", "text_ar": "اَرْشٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T, TA.) [Hence,] one says of the low, abject, or ignominious, and weak,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~amaA huwa A^aronabN", "text_ar": "اـِنَّمَا هُوَ اَرْنَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He is only a hare"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; because that animal cannot defend itself, and even the lark will endeavour to make it its prey. (A, TA.) See another ex. below, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aronabapN", "text_ar": "اَرْنَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". [Hence, also,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aronabu", "text_ar": "الاَرْنَبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the name of (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain constellation,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Lepus,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "comprising twelve stars in its figure, having no observed stars around it, situate beneath the feet of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljab~aAr", "text_ar": "الجَبَّار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Orion"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and facing the west."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Kzw.) ―         -b2-  Also, (K,) or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maronabN", "text_ar": "مَرْنَبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "accord. to the L, (TA,) or both, (M,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaronabN", "text_ar": "يَرْنَبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jura*", "text_ar": "جُرَذ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "large field-rat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (M, L, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like the jerboa,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, L,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having a short tail."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, L, K.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aronabu", "text_ar": "الاَرْنَبُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbaHoriY~u", "text_ar": "البَحْرِىُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", accord. to Kzw,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain marine animal, the head of which is like that of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aronab", "text_ar": "اَرْنَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hare"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and the body like that of a fish:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or, accord. to Ibn-Seenà,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a small testaceous animal, which is of a poisonous quality when drunk"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in water"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: so that, accord. to this explanation, the resemblance [to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Arnb", "text_ar": "ارنب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "commonly so called] is in the name, not the form. (TA.)       -A2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A sort of ornament worn by women."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "M", "A", "K", "Kzw", "Msb", "Mgh", "T", "S", "Lh", "L"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}